{
  "text": "The crystal structure of CsoS1A, which was used in the simulations, contains one SO 4 2\u2212 molecule bound to the amine groups of G43 [CITATION_1] . The same binding is also found in the crystal structures of CcmK1 and CcmK2, which are homologues of CcmK4 [CITATION_2] . For CcmK1 and CcmK2, the serine residues equivalent to S41 of CcmK4 bind a SO 4 2\u2212 molecule. These results all point to the presence of a positive electrostatic potential within the pore attracting negatively charged molecules.",
